text.section:
Upon petition by the cabinet a court may issue an order authorizing the provision of emergency protective services to an adult after a hearing and upon a finding based on a preponderance of the evidence that:
The adult is in a state of abuse, neglect, or exploitation and is living in conditions which present a substantial risk of death or immediate and serious physical harm to himself or others;
The adult is in need of protective services;
The adult lacks the capacity to consent to such services; and
No person authorized by law or court order to give consent for the adult is available to consent to protective services or such person refuses to give consent.
